Note: ============================================================================
Note: MATLAB SEMANTIC ANALYZER
Note: ============================================================================
Note: Semantic analysis for MATLAB scientific/engineering computing language
Note: Handles MATLAB-specific features:
Note: - Matrix operations and vectorization
Note: - Cell arrays and structures
Note: - Function handles and anonymous functions
Note: - Toolbox functions and packages
Note: - Classes and object-oriented programming
Note: - MEX file interfaces
Note: - Simulink integration
Note: - MATLAB App Designer

Import from "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir_nodes.runa" use HIRNode, HIRStatement, HIRExpression, HIRType
Import from "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir_builder.runa" use HIRBuilder

@Reasoning:
The semantic-analysis state object. Models MATLAB's hierarchical workspace
(current + parent_context), the loaded toolbox names, the function being
analyzed, diagnostic lists, a memoized type cache to avoid recomputing
type signatures for repeatedly-referenced functions, registries for class
definitions and function handles, the MATLAB path search list, and the
persistent-variable table separate from the workspace because persistent
vars survive function returns while regular workspace vars do not.
@End Reasoning
Type called "MatlabSemanticContext":
    current_workspace as MatlabWorkspace
    parent_context as MatlabSemanticContext
    loaded_toolboxes as List[String]
    current_function as String
    error_list as List[String]
    warning_list as List[String]
    type_cache as Dictionary[String, MatlabType]
    class_definitions as Dictionary[String, MatlabClassInfo]
    function_handles as Dictionary[String, MatlabFunctionHandle]
    path_directories as List[String]
    persistent_variables as Dictionary[String, MatlabVariable]
End Type

@Reasoning:
A MATLAB scope frame holding variable and function bindings. parent_workspace
implements the chain from a function's local workspace back to base; the
is_base flag identifies the top-of-chain frame and is_function_workspace
distinguishes function-local frames from script-style frames where
assignments persist to the base workspace.
@End Reasoning
Type called "MatlabWorkspace":
    variables as Dictionary[String, MatlabVariable]
    functions as Dictionary[String, MatlabFunction]
    parent_workspace as MatlabWorkspace
    name as String
    is_base as Boolean
    is_function_workspace as Boolean
End Type

Note: Local Matlab AST schema used by this semantic analyzer until v0.0.9.x
Note: replaces the field-rich placeholder with generic HIRNode traversal.
@Reasoning:
Wide-field AST view for the semantic analyzer. Unlike the parser's compact
ASTNode, this exposes named slots per node-kind (function_name, rows,
elements, etc.) so the semantic analyzer can read structure without
knowing positional child layouts. The node_type string is read by
analyze_matlab_node to dispatch; unused fields for a given node-kind
remain at their default integer value (0).
@End Reasoning
Type called "MatlabSemNode":
    node_type as String
    name as Integer
    body as Integer
    statements as Integer
    arguments as Integer
    function_name as Integer
    input_parameters as Integer
    output_parameters as Integer
    output_assignment as Integer
    rows as Integer
    type as Integer
    elements as Integer
    value as Integer
    literal_type as Integer
End Type

Note: A matlab parameter referenced by analyze functions.
@Reasoning:
Lightweight parameter triple (name, type, source line) used by the
analyzer's signature-checking paths. Distinct from the richer
MatlabParameter (which carries varargin/optional flags) so internal
traversals avoid carrying unused fields.
@End Reasoning
Type called "MatlabParam":
    name as Integer
    type as Integer
    line as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Symbol record for one MATLAB variable. Tracks the declared type plus
storage-class flags (global/persistent), source-position bounds (first
assignment / last access) for usage-warning checks, and matrix-specific
runtime traits (dimensions, sparse, complex) needed to choose correct
codegen paths.
@End Reasoning
Type called "MatlabVariable":
    name as String
    type as MatlabType
    is_global as Boolean
    is_persistent as Boolean
    scope as String
    first_assignment_line as Integer
    last_access_line as Integer
    dimensions as List[Integer]
    is_sparse as Boolean
    is_complex as Boolean
End Type

@Reasoning:
Function metadata covering user-defined, built-in, MEX bridge, and
anonymous (lambda) functions. The toolbox field is set only for built-ins
loaded via load_matlab_builtins so the analyzer can validate "function
exists only after toolbox X has been loaded". has_variable_inputs/outputs
track MATLAB's varargin/varargout for arity checking.
@End Reasoning
Type called "MatlabFunction":
    name as String
    input_parameters as List[MatlabParameter]
    output_parameters as List[String]
    return_type as MatlabType
    is_builtin as Boolean
    is_mex as Boolean
    is_anonymous as Boolean
    toolbox as String
    m_file_path as String
    has_variable_inputs as Boolean
    has_variable_outputs as Boolean
End Type

@Reasoning:
A formal-parameter record for MatlabFunction.input_parameters. The
is_varargin flag distinguishes MATLAB's varargin sentinel from a normal
named parameter; default_value is a source-form string that is re-parsed
on demand when a call site omits the parameter.
@End Reasoning
Type called "MatlabParameter":
    name as String
    type as MatlabType
    is_varargin as Boolean
    is_optional as Boolean
    default_value as String
End Type

@Reasoning:
MATLAB's type model rolled into a single record: scalar/matrix base type
plus dimension list, element_type for nested cell arrays, boolean flags for
the "is X-style container" determinations (cell, struct, function handle),
storage qualifiers (sparse, complex), an optional class_name for OOP types,
and struct_fields for record-style data. A null element_type / empty
dimensions denotes a scalar.
@End Reasoning
Type called "MatlabType":
    base_type as String
    dimensions as List[Integer]
    element_type as MatlabType
    is_cell_array as Boolean
    is_struct as Boolean
    is_function_handle as Boolean
    is_sparse as Boolean
    is_complex as Boolean
    class_name as String
    struct_fields as Dictionary[String, MatlabType]
End Type

@Reasoning:
A classdef registration. is_handle_class distinguishes MATLAB's two class
kinds (value vs handle) which have different copy semantics; is_abstract
prevents instantiation; is_sealed prevents further subclassing. The
superclass list supports MATLAB's multiple inheritance.
@End Reasoning
Type called "MatlabClassInfo":
    class_name as String
    superclasses as List[String]
    properties as Dictionary[String, MatlabProperty]
    methods as Dictionary[String, MatlabMethod]
    events as Dictionary[String, MatlabEvent]
    is_handle_class as Boolean
    is_abstract as Boolean
    is_sealed as Boolean
End Type

@Reasoning:
One property in a classdef. The access string is "public" / "protected" /
"private"; is_dependent marks getter-computed properties; is_observable
triggers listener notification; is_transient excludes the property from
serialization. default_value is captured as source text since MATLAB
defaults can be arbitrary expressions evaluated lazily at instance
construction.
@End Reasoning
Type called "MatlabProperty":
    name as String
    type as MatlabType
    access as String
    is_constant as Boolean
    is_dependent as Boolean
    is_observable as Boolean
    is_transient as Boolean
    default_value as String
End Type

@Reasoning:
One method on a classdef. Constructor/destructor are flagged explicitly
because MATLAB infers them from name-matching the class (constructor) and
the special "delete" name (destructor). is_static methods do not receive an
implicit "obj" first parameter, which affects how calls are lowered.
@End Reasoning
Type called "MatlabMethod":
    name as String
    input_parameters as List[MatlabParameter]
    output_parameters as List[String]
    access as String
    is_static as Boolean
    is_abstract as Boolean
    is_sealed as Boolean
    is_constructor as Boolean
    is_destructor as Boolean
End Type

@Reasoning:
A MATLAB class event with separate notify_access and listen_access
attributes — MATLAB allows the trigger and listener-registration
permissions to differ (e.g. private notify, public listen for a one-way
broadcast pattern).
@End Reasoning
Type called "MatlabEvent":
    name as String
    notify_access as String
    listen_access as String
End Type

@Reasoning:
Tracks a "@func" reference or "@(x) expr" anonymous function. The captured
variables list is populated only for anonymous functions — MATLAB captures
the current workspace values into the closure at the @() expression's
evaluation site, so codegen must know which names need to be packaged
into the closure record.
@End Reasoning
Type called "MatlabFunctionHandle":
    name as String
    target_function as String
    parameters as List[String]
    is_anonymous as Boolean
    captured_variables as List[String]
End Type

@Reasoning:
A semantic diagnostic record. severity is "error"/"warning"/"info" and
error_code is a stable identifier (e.g. "MATLAB:undefined") that downstream
tools can pattern-match on without parsing the human-readable message.
@End Reasoning
Type called "MatlabSemanticError":
    message as String
    line as Integer
    column as Integer
    severity as String
    error_code as String
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: MAIN SEMANTIC ANALYSIS ENTRY POINT
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "analyze_matlab_semantics" that takes ast as MatlabSemNode returns MatlabSemanticContext:
    Note: Main entry point for MATLAB semantic analysis

    @Reasoning:
    MATLAB has unique semantic requirements including matrix-oriented
    programming, dynamic typing with strong matrix support, toolbox
    system, and object-oriented features.
    @End Reasoning

    Let context be create_base_matlab_context

    Note: Load core MATLAB functions and toolboxes
    Call load_matlab_builtins with context

    Note: Analyze the AST
    Call analyze_matlab_node with ast and context

    Note: Perform final validation
    Call validate_matlab_semantics with context

    Return context
End Process

@Reasoning:
Constructs the empty analyzer state with the base workspace pre-installed
and the canonical set of MATLAB toolbox names ("matlab", "signal", "image",
"control", "optim", "stats", "symbolic") pre-loaded so toolbox-gated
function lookups succeed by default. Subsequent calls to load_matlab_*
populate the registries with built-in symbols.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_base_matlab_context" that takes nothing returns MatlabSemanticContext:
    Note: Create the base semantic context with MATLAB workspace

    Let base_workspace be a value of type MatlabWorkspace with
        variables as a dictionary containing nothing,
        functions as a dictionary containing nothing,
        parent_workspace as 0,
        name as "base",
        is_base as true,
        is_function_workspace as false

    Let context be a value of type MatlabSemanticContext with
        current_workspace as base_workspace,
        parent_context as 0,
        loaded_toolboxes as a list containing "matlab", "signal", "image", "control", "optim", "stats", "symbolic",
        current_function as 0,
        error_list as a list containing nothing,
        warning_list as a list containing nothing,
        type_cache as a dictionary containing nothing,
        class_definitions as a dictionary containing nothing,
        function_handles as a dictionary containing nothing,
        path_directories as a list containing ".", "/matlab/toolbox",
        persistent_variables as a dictionary containing nothing

    Return context
End Process

Process called "load_matlab_builtins" that takes ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Note: Load core MATLAB built-in functions and types

    @Reasoning:
    MATLAB comes with extensive built-in functions for matrix operations,
    mathematical functions, I/O operations, and graphics. These need to
    be available in the base workspace.
    @End Reasoning

    Note: Load matrix and array functions
    Call load_matrix_functions with ctx
    Call load_mathematical_functions with ctx
    Call load_string_functions with ctx
    Call load_io_functions with ctx
    Call load_graphics_functions with ctx
    Call load_control_flow_functions with ctx

    Note: Load standard data types
    Call load_matlab_types with ctx

    Note: Load classes
    Call load_standard_classes with ctx
End Process

@Reasoning:
Registers MATLAB's core matrix-construction, query, reshape, transpose,
and decomposition built-ins (zeros, ones, eye, rand/randn, size, length,
reshape, transpose, ctranspose, inv, det, eig, svd, qr, chol, pinv). Each
gets a typed signature via create_matlab_function so call sites can be
type-checked against the right number/kind of arguments.
@End Reasoning
Process called "load_matrix_functions" that takes ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Note: Load matrix and array manipulation functions

    Let matrix_functions be a list containing:
        create_matlab_function with "zeros" and create_matrix_creation_function,
        create_matlab_function with "ones" and create_matrix_creation_function,
        create_matlab_function with "eye" and create_identity_matrix_function,
        create_matlab_function with "rand" and create_random_matrix_function,
        create_matlab_function with "randn" and create_normal_random_function,
        create_matlab_function with "size" and create_size_function,
        create_matlab_function with "length" and create_length_function,
        create_matlab_function with "reshape" and create_reshape_function,
        create_matlab_function with "transpose" and create_transpose_function,
        create_matlab_function with "ctranspose" and create_conjugate_transpose_function,
        create_matlab_function with "inv" and create_matrix_inverse_function,
        create_matlab_function with "det" and create_determinant_function,
        create_matlab_function with "eig" and create_eigenvalue_function,
        create_matlab_function with "svd" and create_svd_function,
        create_matlab_function with "qr" and create_qr_function,
        create_matlab_function with "chol" and create_cholesky_function,
        create_matlab_function with "pinv" and create_pseudoinverse_function

    For Each func as MatlabFunction in matrix_functions:
        Set ctx.current_workspace.functions at key func.name to func
    End For
End Process

@Reasoning:
Registers the standard scalar/elementwise math and statistical built-ins:
trig (sin/cos/tan + inverses), transcendental (exp/log/log10/sqrt),
absolute/real/imag/conj/round/floor/ceil, and reductions (sum, mean, std,
var, max, min). These all accept matrix inputs in MATLAB's elementwise
broadcasting semantics.
@End Reasoning
Process called "load_mathematical_functions" that takes ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Note: Load mathematical and statistical functions

    Let math_functions be a list containing:
        create_matlab_function with "sin" and create_trig_function,
        create_matlab_function with "cos" and create_trig_function,
        create_matlab_function with "tan" and create_trig_function,
        create_matlab_function with "asin" and create_inverse_trig_function,
        create_matlab_function with "acos" and create_inverse_trig_function,
        create_matlab_function with "atan" and create_inverse_trig_function,
        create_matlab_function with "exp" and create_exponential_function,
        create_matlab_function with "log" and create_logarithm_function,
        create_matlab_function with "log10" and create_log10_function,
        create_matlab_function with "sqrt" and create_sqrt_function,
        create_matlab_function with "abs" and create_absolute_function,
        create_matlab_function with "real" and create_real_function,
        create_matlab_function with "imag" and create_imaginary_function,
        create_matlab_function with "conj" and create_conjugate_function,
        create_matlab_function with "round" and create_round_function,
        create_matlab_function with "floor" and create_floor_function,
        create_matlab_function with "ceil" and create_ceiling_function,
        create_matlab_function with "sum" and create_sum_function,
        create_matlab_function with "mean" and create_mean_function,
        create_matlab_function with "std" and create_std_function,
        create_matlab_function with "var" and create_variance_function,
        create_matlab_function with "max" and create_max_function,
        create_matlab_function with "min" and create_min_function

    For Each func as MatlabFunction in math_functions:
        Set ctx.current_workspace.functions at key func.name to func
    End For
End Process

@Reasoning:
Registers string manipulation built-ins: formatted I/O (sprintf, fprintf),
comparison (strcmp, strcmpi), concatenation/trim/split/join, and the
String / Char / Double / num2str / str2num conversion family.
@End Reasoning
Process called "load_string_functions" that takes ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Note: Load string manipulation functions

    Let string_functions be a list containing:
        create_matlab_function with "sprintf" and create_sprintf_function,
        create_matlab_function with "fprintf" and create_fprintf_function,
        create_matlab_function with "strcmp" and create_strcmp_function,
        create_matlab_function with "strcmpi" and create_strcmpi_function,
        create_matlab_function with "strcat" and create_strcat_function,
        create_matlab_function with "strtrim" and create_strtrim_function,
        create_matlab_function with "strsplit" and create_strsplit_function,
        create_matlab_function with "strjoin" and create_strjoin_function,
        create_matlab_function with "char" and create_char_function,
        create_matlab_function with "string" and create_string_function,
        create_matlab_function with "double" and create_double_function,
        create_matlab_function with "num2str" and create_num2str_function,
        create_matlab_function with "str2num" and create_str2num_function

    For Each func as MatlabFunction in string_functions:
        Set ctx.current_workspace.functions at key func.name to func
    End For
End Process

@Reasoning:
Registers I/O built-ins: console (disp/fprintf/input), MAT-file
(load/save), delimited text (csvread/csvwrite), spreadsheet (xlsread/
xlswrite), and tabular (readtable/writetable). Note fprintf appears here
and in load_string_functions — MATLAB exposes the same function in both
contexts, and re-registering with the same key is idempotent.
@End Reasoning
Process called "load_io_functions" that takes ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Note: Load input/output functions

    Let io_functions be a list containing:
        create_matlab_function with "disp" and create_disp_function,
        create_matlab_function with "fprintf" and create_fprintf_function,
        create_matlab_function with "input" and create_input_function,
        create_matlab_function with "load" and create_load_function,
        create_matlab_function with "save" and create_save_function,
        create_matlab_function with "csvread" and create_csvread_function,
        create_matlab_function with "csvwrite" and create_csvwrite_function,
        create_matlab_function with "xlsread" and create_xlsread_function,
        create_matlab_function with "xlswrite" and create_xlswrite_function,
        create_matlab_function with "readtable" and create_readtable_function,
        create_matlab_function with "writetable" and create_writetable_function

    For Each func as MatlabFunction in io_functions:
        Set ctx.current_workspace.functions at key func.name to func
    End For
End Process

@Reasoning:
Registers MATLAB's plotting and graphics primitives: 2D (plot, scatter,
bar, histogram), 3D (surf, mesh, contour), figure/subplot/hold/axis
management, and label/title/legend/grid annotations. Necessary so calls
like "plot(x,y)" pass arity checks even though the translator does not
emit any actual graphics code.
@End Reasoning
Process called "load_graphics_functions" that takes ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Note: Load graphics and plotting functions

    Let graphics_functions be a list containing:
        create_matlab_function with "plot" and create_plot_function,
        create_matlab_function with "subplot" and create_subplot_function,
        create_matlab_function with "figure" and create_figure_function,
        create_matlab_function with "hold" and create_hold_function,
        create_matlab_function with "xlabel" and create_xlabel_function,
        create_matlab_function with "ylabel" and create_ylabel_function,
        create_matlab_function with "title" and create_title_function,
        create_matlab_function with "legend" and create_legend_function,
        create_matlab_function with "grid" and create_grid_function,
        create_matlab_function with "axis" and create_axis_function,
        create_matlab_function with "surf" and create_surf_function,
        create_matlab_function with "mesh" and create_mesh_function,
        create_matlab_function with "contour" and create_contour_function,
        create_matlab_function with "histogram" and create_histogram_function,
        create_matlab_function with "bar" and create_bar_function,
        create_matlab_function with "scatter" and create_scatter_function

    For Each func as MatlabFunction in graphics_functions:
        Set ctx.current_workspace.functions at key func.name to func
    End For
End Process

@Reasoning:
Registers error-handling (error/warning/assert), try/catch as
function-like (MATLAB also has them as statements but exposes
identifiers), and the debugger built-ins (keyboard, dbstop, dbcont,
dbstep, dbquit) so debugger references in user code pass undefined-name
checks.
@End Reasoning
Process called "load_control_flow_functions" that takes ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Note: Load control flow and debugging functions

    Let control_functions be a list containing:
        create_matlab_function with "error" and create_error_function,
        create_matlab_function with "warning" and create_warning_function,
        create_matlab_function with "assert" and create_assert_function,
        create_matlab_function with "try" and create_try_function,
        create_matlab_function with "catch" and create_catch_function,
        create_matlab_function with "keyboard" and create_keyboard_function,
        create_matlab_function with "dbstop" and create_dbstop_function,
        create_matlab_function with "dbcont" and create_dbcont_function,
        create_matlab_function with "dbstep" and create_dbstep_function,
        create_matlab_function with "dbquit" and create_dbquit_function

    For Each func as MatlabFunction in control_functions:
        Set ctx.current_workspace.functions at key func.name to func
    End For
End Process

Process called "load_matlab_types" that takes ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Note: Load standard MATLAB data types

    @Reasoning:
    MATLAB has unique data types including double arrays, cell arrays,
    structures, function handles, and various specialized types for
    different toolboxes.
    @End Reasoning

    Note: Register basic MATLAB types
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "double" to create_double_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "single" to create_single_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "logical" to create_logical_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "char" to create_char_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "string" to create_string_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "int8" to create_int8_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "int16" to create_int16_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "int32" to create_int32_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "int64" to create_int64_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "uint8" to create_uint8_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "uint16" to create_uint16_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "uint32" to create_uint32_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "uint64" to create_uint64_type

    Note: Register complex MATLAB types
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "cell" to create_cell_array_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "struct" to create_struct_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "function_handle" to create_function_handle_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "table" to create_table_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "timetable" to create_timetable_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "categorical" to create_categorical_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "datetime" to create_datetime_type
    Set ctx.type_cache at key "duration" to create_duration_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
Orchestrates registration of MATLAB's built-in class hierarchy in three
phases: handle classes (reference semantics), value classes (copy
semantics), and graphics classes (Figure, Axes, Line, etc.). The split
exists because each phase has distinct registration paths in the underlying
register_*_classes helpers.
@End Reasoning
Process called "load_standard_classes" that takes ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Note: Load standard MATLAB classes

    Note: Register handle classes
    Call register_handle_classes with ctx

    Note: Register value classes
    Call register_value_classes with ctx

    Note: Register graphics classes
    Call register_graphics_classes with ctx
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AST NODE ANALYSIS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Polymorphic dispatch on the node's type string. Routes every recognized
AST node kind (Program, function/class/property/method declarations,
all expression forms, control flow) to a specialized analyzer. Unknown
node kinds fall through to analyze_generic_matlab_node which recurses
generically — keeping the dispatch tolerant of new node kinds added by
future parser updates.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_node" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Note: Analyze any MATLAB AST node based on its type

    Match node.type:
        When "Program":
            Call analyze_matlab_program with node and ctx
        When "FunctionDeclaration":
            Call analyze_matlab_function_declaration with node and ctx
        When "VariableDeclaration":
            Call analyze_matlab_variable_declaration with node and ctx
        When "Assignment":
            Call analyze_matlab_assignment with node and ctx
        When "FunctionCall":
            Call analyze_matlab_function_call with node and ctx
        When "MatrixConstruction":
            Call analyze_matlab_matrix_construction with node and ctx
        When "CellArrayConstruction":
            Call analyze_matlab_cell_array_construction with node and ctx
        When "StructConstruction":
            Call analyze_matlab_struct_construction with node and ctx
        When "IndexExpression":
            Call analyze_matlab_index_expression with node and ctx
        When "FunctionHandle":
            Call analyze_matlab_function_handle with node and ctx
        When "AnonymousFunction":
            Call analyze_matlab_anonymous_function with node and ctx
        When "ClassDefinition":
            Call analyze_matlab_class_definition with node and ctx
        When "PropertyDefinition":
            Call analyze_matlab_property_definition with node and ctx
        When "MethodDefinition":
            Call analyze_matlab_method_definition with node and ctx
        When "TryStatement":
            Call analyze_matlab_try_statement with node and ctx
        When "IfStatement":
            Call analyze_matlab_if_statement with node and ctx
        When "ForLoop":
            Call analyze_matlab_for_loop with node and ctx
        When "WhileLoop":
            Call analyze_matlab_while_loop with node and ctx
        Otherwise:
            Call analyze_generic_matlab_node with node and ctx
    End Match
End Process

@Reasoning:
Walks every statement in a Program node, recursing through analyze_node so
each statement gets its kind-specific handling. The context's
current_workspace mutates as analysis enters/exits function and class
scopes, but at program top-level it is the base workspace.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_program" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Note: Analyze MATLAB program (script or function file)

    For Each statement in node.statements:
        Call analyze_matlab_node with statement and ctx
    End For
End Process

Process called "analyze_matlab_function_declaration" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Note: Analyze MATLAB function declaration

    @Reasoning:
    MATLAB functions have unique characteristics including multiple output
    parameters, variable inputs/outputs (varargin/varargout), nested functions,
    and special scoping rules.
    @End Reasoning

    Let func_name be node.name
    Let input_params be node.input_parameters
    Let output_params be node.output_parameters
    Let body be node.body

    Note: Create function workspace
    Let func_workspace be create_function_workspace with ctx.current_workspace and func_name

    Note: Analyze input parameters
    Let matlab_inputs be a list containing nothing
    For Each param in input_params:
        Let matlab_param be analyze_matlab_parameter with param and ctx
        Add matlab_param to end of matlab_inputs

        Note: Add parameter to function workspace
        Let param_var be a value of type MatlabVariable with
            name as param.name,
            type as matlab_param.type,
            is_global as false,
            is_persistent as false,
            scope as func_name,
            first_assignment_line as param.line,
            last_access_line as param.line,
            dimensions as a list containing nothing,
            is_sparse as false,
            is_complex as false

        Set func_workspace.variables at key param.name to param_var
    End For

    Note: Analyze output parameters
    Let output_names be a list containing nothing
    For Each output_param in output_params:
        Add output_param.name to end of output_names

        Note: Create output variable in workspace
        Let output_var be a value of type MatlabVariable with
            name as output_param.name,
            type as create_any_matlab_type,
            is_global as false,
            is_persistent as false,
            scope as func_name,
            first_assignment_line as output_param.line,
            last_access_line as output_param.line,
            dimensions as a list containing nothing,
            is_sparse as false,
            is_complex as false

        Set func_workspace.variables at key output_param.name to output_var
    End For

    Note: Create function object
    Let inferred_return_type be infer_matlab_return_type with output_params
    Let has_varargin be check_has_varargin with input_params
    Let has_varargout be check_has_varargout with output_params
    Let matlab_function be a value of type MatlabFunction with
        name as func_name,
        input_parameters as matlab_inputs,
        output_parameters as output_names,
        return_type as inferred_return_type,
        is_builtin as false,
        is_mex as false,
        is_anonymous as false,
        toolbox as 0,
        m_file_path as 0,
        has_variable_inputs as has_varargin,
        has_variable_outputs as has_varargout

    Note: Set function context and analyze body
    Let old_workspace be ctx.current_workspace
    Let old_func be ctx.current_function
    Set ctx.current_workspace to func_workspace
    Set ctx.current_function to func_name

    Call analyze_matlab_node with body and ctx

    Note: Restore context
    Set ctx.current_workspace to old_workspace
    Set ctx.current_function to old_func

    Note: Register function in workspace
    Set ctx.current_workspace.functions at key func_name to matlab_function
End Process

Process called "analyze_matlab_matrix_construction" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Note: Analyze MATLAB matrix construction [1 2; 3 4]

    @Reasoning:
    MATLAB matrix construction has specific rules for dimension compatibility,
    semicolon for row separation, space/comma for column separation, and
    automatic type promotion.
    @End Reasoning

    Let rows be node.rows
    Let expected_columns be -1

    For Each row as MatlabSemNode in rows:
        Let elements be row.elements
        Let column_count be length of elements

        Note: Check column consistency
        If expected_columns is equal to -1:
            Set expected_columns to column_count
        Otherwise If expected_columns is not equal to column_count:
            Let error be "Matrix dimensions must agree - row has " joined with string representation of column_count joined with " columns, expected " joined with string representation of expected_columns
            Add error to end of ctx.error_list
        End If

        Note: Analyze each element
        For Each element in elements:
            Call analyze_matlab_node with element and ctx
        End For
    End For
End Process

@Reasoning:
Resolves a function-call site against the workspace chain. If the bare
lookup fails, falls back to check_method_call to handle dispatch through
class instances or constructor invocation. Truly undefined names produce
an "Undefined function or variable" error matching MATLAB's own
diagnostic. After resolution, each argument is recursively analyzed and
the full call is validated against the function's declared arity/types.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_function_call" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Note: Analyze MATLAB function call

    Let func_name be node.function_name
    Let arguments be node.arguments
    Let output_assignment be node.output_assignment

    Note: Check if function exists
    Let matlab_function be lookup_matlab_function with func_name and ctx
    If matlab_function is equal to 0:
        Note: Check for method call or class constructor
        Let method_function be check_method_call with func_name and arguments and ctx
        If method_function is not equal to 0:
            Set matlab_function to method_function
        End If
    End If

    If matlab_function is equal to 0:
        Let error be "Undefined function or variable '" joined with func_name joined with "'"
        Add error to end of ctx.error_list
        Return
    End If

    Note: Analyze arguments
    For Each arg in arguments:
        Call analyze_matlab_node with arg and ctx
    End For

    Note: Validate argument count and types
    Call validate_matlab_function_arguments with matlab_function and arguments and ctx

    Note: Handle output assignment
    If output_assignment is not equal to 0:
        Call analyze_matlab_output_assignment with output_assignment and matlab_function and ctx
    End If
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TYPE INFERENCE AND VALIDATION
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "infer_matlab_expression_type" that takes expr as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns MatlabType:
    Note: Infer the type of a MATLAB expression

    @Reasoning:
    MATLAB has dynamic typing but strong matrix orientation. Most operations
    result in double arrays unless explicitly specified otherwise. Type
    inference helps with optimization and error detection.
    @End Reasoning

    Match expr.type:
        When "Literal":
            Return infer_matlab_literal_type with expr
        When "Identifier":
            Return infer_matlab_identifier_type with expr and ctx
        When "FunctionCall":
            Return infer_matlab_function_call_type with expr and ctx
        When "MatrixConstruction":
            Return infer_matlab_matrix_type with expr and ctx
        When "CellArrayConstruction":
            Return create_cell_array_type
        When "StructConstruction":
            Return create_struct_type
        When "IndexExpression":
            Return infer_matlab_index_type with expr and ctx
        When "BinaryOperation":
            Return infer_matlab_binary_operation_type with expr and ctx
        When "UnaryOperation":
            Return infer_matlab_unary_operation_type with expr and ctx
        When "FunctionHandle":
            Return create_function_handle_type
        Otherwise:
            Return create_any_matlab_type
    End Match
End Process

@Reasoning:
Maps literal_type strings ("double", "single", "logical", "char", "string",
"integer") to constructed MatlabType records. Integer literals default to
double per MATLAB's "all numerics start as double unless cast" rule;
explicit casts produce different literal_type tags from the parser.
@End Reasoning
Process called "infer_matlab_literal_type" that takes expr as MatlabSemNode returns MatlabType:
    Note: Infer type from literal values

    Let value be expr.value
    Let literal_type be expr.literal_type

    Match literal_type:
        When "double":
            Return create_double_type
        When "single":
            Return create_single_type
        When "logical":
            Return create_logical_type
        When "char":
            Return create_char_type
        When "string":
            Return create_string_type
        When "integer":
            Return create_double_type
        Otherwise:
            Return create_double_type
    End Match
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: HELPER FUNCTIONS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Walks the workspace chain (current_workspace -> parent_workspace -> ...
-> base) looking for a function binding. The chain walk implements MATLAB's
lexical-scope resolution for function definitions. Returns null when the
name is not found in any frame so the caller can issue a precise
diagnostic.
@End Reasoning
Process called "lookup_matlab_function" that takes name as String, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns MatlabFunction:
    Note: Look up function in workspace chain

    Let current_workspace be ctx.current_workspace
    While current_workspace is not equal to 0:
        If current_workspace.functions contains key name:
            Return current_workspace.functions at key name
        End If
        Set current_workspace to current_workspace.parent_workspace
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Workspace chain walk for variable bindings, with a post-loop fallback to
the persistent_variables registry. Persistent variables live outside the
normal workspace chain because they survive function returns — so a chain
walk would not find them and the second lookup handles that case.
@End Reasoning
Process called "lookup_matlab_variable" that takes name as String, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns MatlabVariable:
    Note: Look up variable in workspace chain

    Let current_workspace be ctx.current_workspace
    While current_workspace is not equal to 0:
        If current_workspace.variables contains key name:
            Return current_workspace.variables at key name
        End If
        Set current_workspace to current_workspace.parent_workspace
    End While

    Note: Check persistent variables
    If ctx.persistent_variables contains key name:
        Return ctx.persistent_variables at key name
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Constructs a new function-local workspace linked to its caller (parent).
Functions get is_function_workspace=true so analyze code can distinguish
function-scoped assignments (which die at return) from script-scoped
assignments (which persist).
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_function_workspace" that takes parent as MatlabWorkspace, func_name as String returns MatlabWorkspace:
    Note: Create new workspace for function scope

    Return a value of type MatlabWorkspace with
        variables as a dictionary containing nothing,
        functions as a dictionary containing nothing,
        parent_workspace as parent,
        name as func_name,
        is_base as false,
        is_function_workspace as true
End Process

Process called "validate_matlab_semantics" that takes ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Note: Perform final semantic validation

    @Reasoning:
    Final validation checks for MATLAB-specific issues such as undefined
    variables, dimension mismatches, toolbox dependencies, and class
    hierarchy problems.
    @End Reasoning

    Call validate_matlab_variable_usage with ctx
    Call validate_matlab_function_usage with ctx
    Call validate_matlab_toolbox_dependencies with ctx
    Call validate_matlab_class_definitions with ctx
    Call validate_matlab_matrix_operations with ctx
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TYPE CREATION HELPERS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Factory for MATLAB's primary numeric type: scalar double (no dimensions,
not sparse, not complex). All numeric literals default to this; callers
mutate the result to attach dimensions if they later determine the value
is matrix-shaped.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_double_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return a value of type MatlabType with
        base_type as "double",
        dimensions as 0,
        element_type as 0,
        is_cell_array as false,
        is_struct as false,
        is_function_handle as false,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as false,
        class_name as 0,
        struct_fields as 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Factory for MATLAB's "logical" type — a 1-bit Boolean produced by
comparison operators, logical functions, and the true/false constants.
Distinct from "double" with values 0/1 because MATLAB allows logical
arrays to index into other arrays.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_logical_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return a value of type MatlabType with
        base_type as "logical",
        dimensions as 0,
        element_type as 0,
        is_cell_array as false,
        is_struct as false,
        is_function_handle as false,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as false,
        class_name as 0,
        struct_fields as 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Factory for MATLAB's "char" type — the character-array form produced by
single-quoted literals. Distinct from "string" because MATLAB historically
had only char arrays; string-class was added in R2017a as a separate
type with object-like semantics.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_char_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return a value of type MatlabType with
        base_type as "char",
        dimensions as 0,
        element_type as 0,
        is_cell_array as false,
        is_struct as false,
        is_function_handle as false,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as false,
        class_name as 0,
        struct_fields as 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Factory for MATLAB's "cell" type — a heterogeneous container indexed with
curly braces (a{i,j}). is_cell_array=true is set so consumers can branch
between matrix indexing and cell extraction at codegen.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_cell_array_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return a value of type MatlabType with
        base_type as "cell",
        dimensions as 0,
        element_type as create_any_matlab_type,
        is_cell_array as true,
        is_struct as false,
        is_function_handle as false,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as false,
        class_name as 0,
        struct_fields as 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Factory for MATLAB's "struct" type — named-field records accessed via
"obj.field". is_struct=true. struct_fields is left null on creation and
populated later as field assignments are observed during AST walk.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_struct_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return a value of type MatlabType with
        base_type as "struct",
        dimensions as 0,
        element_type as 0,
        is_cell_array as false,
        is_struct as true,
        is_function_handle as false,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as false,
        class_name as 0,
        struct_fields as a dictionary containing nothing
End Process

@Reasoning:
Factory for MATLAB's "function_handle" type — the result of "@name" or
"@(x) body". is_function_handle=true. Used by infer_matlab_expression_type
to type FunctionHandle AST nodes; the actual captured-name/lambda-body
details live in a MatlabFunctionHandle entry registered separately in
ctx.function_handles.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_function_handle_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return a value of type MatlabType with
        base_type as "function_handle",
        dimensions as 0,
        element_type as 0,
        is_cell_array as false,
        is_struct as false,
        is_function_handle as true,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as false,
        class_name as 0,
        struct_fields as 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Factory for the "any" sentinel type. Returned when type inference cannot
determine a more specific type (e.g. for unbound output variables before
their first assignment, or for the result of an unresolved function call).
The "any" type passes all type checks, deferring the actual narrowing to
runtime — matching MATLAB's dynamic-typing semantics.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_any_matlab_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return a value of type MatlabType with
        base_type as "any",
        dimensions as 0,
        element_type as 0,
        is_cell_array as false,
        is_struct as false,
        is_function_handle as false,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as false,
        class_name as 0,
        struct_fields as 0
End Process

Note: Entry point for MATLAB semantic analysis
@Reasoning:
Thin wrapper over analyze_matlab_semantics that exposes a stable public
name. Provided so callers can use the more descriptive "semantic_tree"
verb without depending on the internal "semantics" entry point name.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_semantic_tree" that takes ast as MatlabSemNode returns MatlabSemanticContext:
    Return analyze_matlab_semantics with ast
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: BUILTIN REGISTRATION ADAPTER
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Adapter mirroring the other frontends' create_*_function name-stamping
helper. The load_*_functions tables call create_matlab_function with a
canonical MATLAB identifier and a freshly built MatlabFunction signature
(produced by a create_*_function factory). The factories construct a
shape-correct parameter list and return type but seed an internal default
name; this routine overwrites that with the authoritative MATLAB name so
lookup_matlab_function resolves the exact call site, and stamps is_builtin
plus the "matlab" toolbox so toolbox-dependency validation can attribute
the symbol to its providing toolbox.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_matlab_function" that takes name as String, func as MatlabFunction returns MatlabFunction:
    Set func.name to name
    Set func.is_builtin to true
    If func.toolbox is equal to 0:
        Set func.toolbox to "matlab"
    End If
    Return func
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SCALAR / NUMERIC TYPE FACTORIES
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Factory for MATLAB's "single" type — 32-bit IEEE-754 float produced by
single() casts. Distinct from "double" so codegen selects the 4-byte
storage width and the narrower arithmetic path.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_single_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return a value of type MatlabType with
        base_type as "single",
        dimensions as 0,
        element_type as 0,
        is_cell_array as false,
        is_struct as false,
        is_function_handle as false,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as false,
        class_name as 0,
        struct_fields as 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Factory for MATLAB's string-class scalar (R2017a string objects). Distinct
from char arrays: string values carry one text element per array cell and
support object-style methods, so base_type "string" branches codegen to
the string-object representation rather than a char buffer.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_string_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return a value of type MatlabType with
        base_type as "string",
        dimensions as 0,
        element_type as 0,
        is_cell_array as false,
        is_struct as false,
        is_function_handle as false,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as false,
        class_name as 0,
        struct_fields as 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Factory for a signed N-bit integer MatlabType. MATLAB's int8/16/32/64 are
saturating fixed-width integers; the width is captured in base_type so
codegen picks the right storage and saturation arithmetic. Shared by the
four signed-integer factories below.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_signed_integer_type" that takes width as String returns MatlabType:
    Return a value of type MatlabType with
        base_type as width,
        dimensions as 0,
        element_type as 0,
        is_cell_array as false,
        is_struct as false,
        is_function_handle as false,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as false,
        class_name as 0,
        struct_fields as 0
End Process

Process called "create_int8_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return create_signed_integer_type with "int8"
End Process

Process called "create_int16_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return create_signed_integer_type with "int16"
End Process

Process called "create_int32_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return create_signed_integer_type with "int32"
End Process

Process called "create_int64_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return create_signed_integer_type with "int64"
End Process

Process called "create_uint8_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return create_signed_integer_type with "uint8"
End Process

Process called "create_uint16_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return create_signed_integer_type with "uint16"
End Process

Process called "create_uint32_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return create_signed_integer_type with "uint32"
End Process

Process called "create_uint64_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return create_signed_integer_type with "uint64"
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONTAINER / TOOLBOX TYPE FACTORIES
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Factory for MATLAB's "table" type — column-oriented tabular container with
named variables. struct_fields holds the per-column type map (populated as
the analyzer observes assignments to t.Var) so column access can be
type-checked; the table behaves struct-like for dot access, hence
struct_fields is an empty dictionary rather than null.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_table_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return a value of type MatlabType with
        base_type as "table",
        dimensions as 0,
        element_type as 0,
        is_cell_array as false,
        is_struct as true,
        is_function_handle as false,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as false,
        class_name as "table",
        struct_fields as a dictionary containing nothing
End Process

@Reasoning:
Factory for "timetable" — a table whose row index is a datetime/duration
RowTimes axis. Modelled like table (struct-style column access) but tagged
with class_name "timetable" so time-axis operations (retime, synchronize)
resolve to the correct method set.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_timetable_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return a value of type MatlabType with
        base_type as "timetable",
        dimensions as 0,
        element_type as 0,
        is_cell_array as false,
        is_struct as true,
        is_function_handle as false,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as false,
        class_name as "timetable",
        struct_fields as a dictionary containing nothing
End Process

@Reasoning:
Factory for "categorical" — an enumerated label array backed by an
integer index into a category list. element_type is char (the label
representation) so comparisons against char literals type-check; base_type
records the categorical nature for codegen of the index table.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_categorical_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return a value of type MatlabType with
        base_type as "categorical",
        dimensions as 0,
        element_type as create_char_type,
        is_cell_array as false,
        is_struct as false,
        is_function_handle as false,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as false,
        class_name as "categorical",
        struct_fields as 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Factory for "datetime" — a point-in-time value supporting arithmetic that
yields durations. class_name "datetime" routes method dispatch; base_type
records the temporal kind so datetime minus datetime infers a duration
result rather than a double.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_datetime_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return a value of type MatlabType with
        base_type as "datetime",
        dimensions as 0,
        element_type as 0,
        is_cell_array as false,
        is_struct as false,
        is_function_handle as false,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as false,
        class_name as "datetime",
        struct_fields as 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Factory for "duration" — an elapsed-time span (the result of datetime
subtraction). class_name "duration" enables duration-aware arithmetic and
formatting; base_type records the span kind so duration plus datetime
infers a datetime result.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_duration_type" that takes nothing returns MatlabType:
    Return a value of type MatlabType with
        base_type as "duration",
        dimensions as 0,
        element_type as 0,
        is_cell_array as false,
        is_struct as false,
        is_function_handle as false,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as false,
        class_name as "duration",
        struct_fields as 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: BUILTIN SIGNATURE CONSTRUCTION HELPERS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Builds one formal MatlabParameter with the given name and type, marked as a
normal (non-varargin, non-optional) required parameter. Centralizes the
parameter-record shape so every builtin signature factory constructs
parameters identically.
@End Reasoning
Process called "make_matlab_param" that takes pname as String, ptype as MatlabType returns MatlabParameter:
    Return a value of type MatlabParameter with
        name as pname,
        type as ptype,
        is_varargin as false,
        is_optional as false,
        default_value as ""
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builds an optional MatlabParameter (a trailing argument a call site may
omit). default_value carries the source-form default re-parsed on demand;
is_optional=true lets validate_matlab_function_arguments treat a missing
positional as legal.
@End Reasoning
Process called "make_matlab_optional_param" that takes pname as String, ptype as MatlabType, dflt as String returns MatlabParameter:
    Return a value of type MatlabParameter with
        name as pname,
        type as ptype,
        is_varargin as false,
        is_optional as true,
        default_value as dflt
End Process

@Reasoning:
Builds the varargin sentinel parameter. is_varargin=true tells arity
checking to accept any number of trailing arguments, matching MATLAB's
varargin semantics where remaining positionals are packed into a cell.
@End Reasoning
Process called "make_matlab_varargin_param" that takes nothing returns MatlabParameter:
    Return a value of type MatlabParameter with
        name as "varargin",
        type as create_cell_array_type,
        is_varargin as true,
        is_optional as true,
        default_value as ""
End Process

@Reasoning:
Assembles a MatlabFunction signature record from a parameter list and a
return type. The name is seeded to a placeholder that create_matlab_function
overwrites with the authoritative MATLAB identifier at registration; the
varargin/varargout flags are derived from the supplied flags so arity
checking knows the call shape. Centralizes signature construction for every
builtin factory.
@End Reasoning
Process called "make_matlab_signature" that takes params as List[MatlabParameter], ret as MatlabType, varin as Boolean, varout as Boolean returns MatlabFunction:
    Let out_names be a list containing nothing
    Return a value of type MatlabFunction with
        name as "builtin",
        input_parameters as params,
        output_parameters as out_names,
        return_type as ret,
        is_builtin as true,
        is_mex as false,
        is_anonymous as false,
        toolbox as "matlab",
        m_file_path as "",
        has_variable_inputs as varin,
        has_variable_outputs as varout
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: MATRIX BUILTIN SIGNATURE FACTORIES
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
zeros/ones accept a variadic list of dimension sizes (zeros(3), zeros(3,4),
zeros([3 4])) and an optional class-name string, returning a double matrix.
Modelled with a varargin tail so any dimension arity passes; the result is
a double array.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_matrix_creation_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Let dims be make_matlab_varargin_param
    Let params be a list containing dims
    Return make_matlab_signature with params, create_double_type, true, false
End Process

@Reasoning:
eye(n) / eye(m,n) builds an identity matrix; takes one required size plus an
