    Return create_unary_double_function
End Process

Process called "create_sqrt_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Return create_unary_double_function
End Process

@Reasoning:
abs(x) returns the magnitude; for complex input the result is real, so the
return is always a (non-complex) double array.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_absolute_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Return create_unary_double_function
End Process

Process called "create_real_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Return create_unary_double_function
End Process

Process called "create_imaginary_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Return create_unary_double_function
End Process

@Reasoning:
conj(x) returns the complex conjugate; the result preserves the complex
nature of the input, so the factory returns a double type that downstream
inference can mark complex when the argument is complex.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_conjugate_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Return create_unary_double_function
End Process

Process called "create_round_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Return create_unary_double_function
End Process

Process called "create_floor_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Return create_unary_double_function
End Process

Process called "create_ceiling_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Return create_unary_double_function
End Process

@Reasoning:
Shared factory for reductions (sum/prod/mean/std/var/max/min). Each accepts
