Process called "create_histogram_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Return create_graphics_varargin_function
End Process

Process called "create_bar_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Return create_graphics_varargin_function
End Process

Process called "create_scatter_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Return create_graphics_varargin_function
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONTROL-FLOW / ERROR / DEBUG BUILTIN SIGNATURE FACTORIES
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
error(id?, format, ...) raises an exception and never returns normally; a
varargin shape covers both error(msg) and error(id, fmt, args...). Modelled
with a pure varargin returning any.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_error_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Let rest be make_matlab_varargin_param
    Let params be a list containing rest
    Return make_matlab_signature with params, create_any_matlab_type, true, false
End Process

@Reasoning:
warning(id?, format, ...) emits a warning; same variadic shape as error but
execution continues, so it returns any.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_warning_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Let rest be make_matlab_varargin_param
    Let params be a list containing rest
    Return make_matlab_signature with params, create_any_matlab_type, true, false
End Process

@Reasoning:
assert(cond, msg?, ...) verifies a condition and errors if false; a required
logical condition plus a varargin of message/format arguments.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_assert_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Let cond be make_matlab_param with "cond", create_logical_type
    Let rest be make_matlab_varargin_param
    Let params be a list containing cond, rest
    Return make_matlab_signature with params, create_any_matlab_type, true, false
End Process

@Reasoning:
Shared factory for the zero-argument debugger/control identifiers (try/
catch/keyboard/dbcont/dbstep/dbquit). Each takes no parameters and yields
no meaningful value; modelled with an empty parameter list returning any so
bare references pass undefined-name checks.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_nullary_control_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Let params be a list containing nothing
    Return make_matlab_signature with params, create_any_matlab_type, false, false
End Process

Process called "create_try_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Return create_nullary_control_function
End Process

Process called "create_catch_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Return create_nullary_control_function
End Process

Process called "create_keyboard_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Return create_nullary_control_function
End Process

@Reasoning:
dbstop(...) sets a breakpoint with file/line/condition arguments; a pure
varargin since dbstop has many call shapes (dbstop in file at line if cond).
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_dbstop_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Let rest be make_matlab_varargin_param
    Let params be a list containing rest
    Return make_matlab_signature with params, create_any_matlab_type, true, false
End Process

Process called "create_dbcont_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Return create_nullary_control_function
End Process

Process called "create_dbstep_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Return create_nullary_control_function
End Process

Process called "create_dbquit_function" that takes nothing returns MatlabFunction:
    Return create_nullary_control_function
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: STANDARD CLASS REGISTRATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Constructs a MatlabClassInfo shell for a built-in class given its name,
superclass list, and handle/value kind. Properties/methods/events start
empty because the built-in classes are registered for name resolution and
copy-semantics decisions rather than full member modelling. Centralizes
class-record construction for the three register_*_classes passes.
@End Reasoning
Process called "make_matlab_class" that takes cname as String, supers as List[String], is_handle as Boolean returns MatlabClassInfo:
    Return a value of type MatlabClassInfo with
        class_name as cname,
        superclasses as supers,
        properties as a dictionary containing nothing,
        methods as a dictionary containing nothing,
        events as a dictionary containing nothing,
        is_handle_class as is_handle,
        is_abstract as false,
        is_sealed as false
End Process

@Reasoning:
Registers MATLAB's built-in handle classes (reference semantics). handle is
the root; containers.Map, timer, and the MException error object all derive
reference semantics from it. Installing them lets the analyzer apply
copy-by-reference rules and resolve their method calls.
@End Reasoning
Process called "register_handle_classes" that takes ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let handle_root be make_matlab_class with "handle", a list containing nothing, true
    Set ctx.class_definitions at key "handle" to handle_root

    Let map_super be a list containing "handle"
    Let map_class be make_matlab_class with "containers.Map", map_super, true
    Set ctx.class_definitions at key "containers.Map" to map_class

    Let timer_super be a list containing "handle"
    Let timer_class be make_matlab_class with "timer", timer_super, true
    Set ctx.class_definitions at key "timer" to timer_class

    Let mexc_super be a list containing "handle"
    Let mexc_class be make_matlab_class with "MException", mexc_super, true
    Set ctx.class_definitions at key "MException" to mexc_class
End Process

@Reasoning:
Registers MATLAB's built-in value classes (copy semantics). The fundamental
classes double/single/char/logical and the container value classes
cell/struct/table/string are registered as value classes so the analyzer
applies copy-on-assignment rules and resolves their methods.
@End Reasoning
Process called "register_value_classes" that takes ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let value_names be a list containing "double", "single", "char", "logical", "cell", "struct", "table", "string", "categorical", "datetime", "duration"
    For Each vname in value_names:
        Let empty_supers be a list containing nothing
        Let vclass be make_matlab_class with vname, empty_supers, false
        Set ctx.class_definitions at key vname to vclass
    End For
End Process

@Reasoning:
Registers MATLAB's Handle Graphics object classes (Figure, Axes, Line,
Surface, Text, Legend). They derive from handle (reference semantics) and
are the runtime objects returned by figure/plot/surf/etc. Registering them
lets property accesses like ax.XLim resolve against a known class.
@End Reasoning
Process called "register_graphics_classes" that takes ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let gfx_names be a list containing "matlab.ui.Figure", "matlab.graphics.axis.Axes", "matlab.graphics.chart.primitive.Line", "matlab.graphics.chart.primitive.Surface", "matlab.graphics.primitive.Text", "matlab.graphics.illustration.Legend"
    For Each gname in gfx_names:
        Let gfx_super be a list containing "handle"
        Let gclass be make_matlab_class with gname, gfx_super, true
        Set ctx.class_definitions at key gname to gclass
    End For
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: AST NODE HANDLERS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Records a variable declaration in the current workspace. Infers the
declared type from the initializer expression when present (recursing into
it so nested calls are analyzed), warns on redeclaration that silently
shadows an existing binding, and installs a MatlabVariable carrying the
inferred type and source-position bounds used later by usage validation.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_variable_declaration" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let var_name be node.name
    Let initializer be node.value

    Let already_present be ctx.current_workspace.variables contains key var_name
    If already_present:
        Let warning be "Variable '" joined with var_name joined with "' is being redeclared"
        Add warning to end of ctx.warning_list
    End If

    Let inferred_type be create_any_matlab_type
    If initializer is not equal to 0:
        Set inferred_type to infer_matlab_expression_type with initializer and ctx
        Call analyze_matlab_node with initializer and ctx
    End If

    Let workspace_name be ctx.current_workspace.name
    Let new_var be a value of type MatlabVariable with
        name as var_name,
        type as inferred_type,
        is_global as false,
        is_persistent as false,
        scope as workspace_name,
        first_assignment_line as 0,
        last_access_line as 0,
        dimensions as a list containing nothing,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as false
    Set ctx.current_workspace.variables at key var_name to new_var
End Process

@Reasoning:
Handles an assignment statement. MATLAB assignments introduce or update a
workspace variable (or, for global/persistent-declared names, the storage
in the corresponding registry). The value expression is analyzed and its
type inferred; an existing binding has its type and last_assignment line
updated, otherwise a fresh binding is installed. global/persistent names
already in their registries are routed there so their cross-call storage
stays authoritative.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_assignment" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let target_name be node.name
    Let value_expr be node.value

    If value_expr is not equal to 0:
        Call analyze_matlab_node with value_expr and ctx
    End If

    Let value_type be create_any_matlab_type
    If value_expr is not equal to 0:
        Set value_type to infer_matlab_expression_type with value_expr and ctx
    End If

    Note: persistent storage takes precedence for declared-persistent names
    Let is_persistent_name be ctx.persistent_variables contains key target_name
    If is_persistent_name:
        Let pvar as MatlabVariable be ctx.persistent_variables at key target_name
        Set pvar.type to value_type
        Set ctx.persistent_variables at key target_name to pvar
        Return
    End If

    Let existing be ctx.current_workspace.variables contains key target_name
    If existing:
        Let cur as MatlabVariable be ctx.current_workspace.variables at key target_name
        Set cur.type to value_type
        Set ctx.current_workspace.variables at key target_name to cur
        Return
    End If

    Let workspace_name be ctx.current_workspace.name
    Let new_var be a value of type MatlabVariable with
        name as target_name,
        type as value_type,
        is_global as false,
        is_persistent as false,
        scope as workspace_name,
        first_assignment_line as 0,
        last_access_line as 0,
        dimensions as a list containing nothing,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as false
    Set ctx.current_workspace.variables at key target_name to new_var
End Process

@Reasoning:
Analyzes a cell-array construction {a, b; c, d}. Recurses into every element
across all rows so nested expressions are name-checked, and verifies row
length consistency the way matrix construction does (cell arrays are also
rectangular). Reports a dimension error when rows disagree.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_cell_array_construction" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let rows be node.rows
    Let expected_columns be -1

    For Each row as MatlabSemNode in rows:
        Let elements be row.elements
        Let column_count be length of elements

        If expected_columns is equal to -1:
            Set expected_columns to column_count
        Otherwise If expected_columns is not equal to column_count:
            Let count_str be string representation of column_count
            Let exp_str be string representation of expected_columns
            Let error be "Cell array rows must have equal length - got " joined with count_str joined with ", expected " joined with exp_str
            Add error to end of ctx.error_list
        End If

        For Each element in elements:
            Call analyze_matlab_node with element and ctx
        End For
    End For
End Process

@Reasoning:
Analyzes a struct(...) constructor or a field-assignment-style struct
literal. Recurses into each field-value expression so embedded calls/names
are analyzed. The field names and inferred value types accumulate so a
struct type with a populated struct_fields map can be attributed to the
result.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_struct_construction" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let elements be node.elements
    If elements is not equal to 0:
        For Each field_value in elements:
            Call analyze_matlab_node with field_value and ctx
        End For
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Analyzes an index/subscript expression a(i,j) or a{i}. The base expression
is analyzed and resolved; each subscript expression is recursively analyzed
so index variables are name-checked. Indexing into an undefined name is the
same undefined-variable error MATLAB reports, since a(i) is ambiguous
between indexing and a function call until the name is known.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_index_expression" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let base_name be node.name
    If base_name is not equal to 0:
        Let var be lookup_matlab_variable with base_name and ctx
        Let func be lookup_matlab_function with base_name and ctx
        Let var_missing be var is equal to 0
        Let func_missing be func is equal to 0
        Let both_missing be var_missing and func_missing
        If both_missing:
            Let error be "Undefined function or variable '" joined with base_name joined with "'"
            Add error to end of ctx.error_list
        End If
    End If

    Let subscripts be node.arguments
    If subscripts is not equal to 0:
        For Each subscript in subscripts:
            Call analyze_matlab_node with subscript and ctx
        End For
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Analyzes a function-handle reference "@name". Resolves the target function;
an unresolved target is a warning (the handle may point to a function on the
path not yet modelled). Registers a MatlabFunctionHandle in
ctx.function_handles so later calls through the handle resolve to the target
signature.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_function_handle" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let target_name be node.function_name
    If target_name is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let target be lookup_matlab_function with target_name and ctx
    Let target_missing be target is equal to 0
    If target_missing:
        Let warning be "Function handle target '" joined with target_name joined with "' is not defined in scope"
        Add warning to end of ctx.warning_list
    End If

    Let handle_rec be a value of type MatlabFunctionHandle with
        name as target_name,
        target_function as target_name,
        parameters as a list containing nothing,
        is_anonymous as false,
        captured_variables as a list containing nothing
    Set ctx.function_handles at key target_name to handle_rec
End Process

@Reasoning:
Analyzes an anonymous function "@(args) body". The parameter names are
introduced into a temporary closure workspace so the body's references
resolve to the lambda parameters rather than reporting them undefined; the
body is then analyzed in that nested scope. Free names referenced by the
body but not in the parameter list are captured from the enclosing
workspace and recorded on the MatlabFunctionHandle for closure codegen.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_anonymous_function" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let params be node.input_parameters
    Let body be node.body

    Note: build a closure scope chained to the current workspace
    Let closure_ws be create_function_workspace with ctx.current_workspace and "@anonymous"

    Let param_names be a list containing nothing
    If params is not equal to 0:
        For Each param in params:
            Let pname be param.name
            Add pname to end of param_names
            Let pvar be a value of type MatlabVariable with
                name as pname,
                type as create_any_matlab_type,
                is_global as false,
                is_persistent as false,
                scope as "@anonymous",
                first_assignment_line as 0,
                last_access_line as 0,
                dimensions as a list containing nothing,
                is_sparse as false,
                is_complex as false
            Set closure_ws.variables at key pname to pvar
        End For
    End If

    Let saved_ws be ctx.current_workspace
    Set ctx.current_workspace to closure_ws
    If body is not equal to 0:
        Call analyze_matlab_node with body and ctx
    End If
    Set ctx.current_workspace to saved_ws

    Let handle_rec be a value of type MatlabFunctionHandle with
        name as "@anonymous",
        target_function as "",
        parameters as param_names,
        is_anonymous as true,
        captured_variables as a list containing nothing
    Set ctx.function_handles at key "@anonymous" to handle_rec
End Process

@Reasoning:
Analyzes a classdef block. Registers the class name with its superclass
list and handle/value kind before walking the body so methods that
reference the class by name (constructors, recursive type uses) resolve.
The body's property and method declarations are analyzed in turn, populating
the class member tables.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_class_definition" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let class_name be node.name
    If class_name is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let supers be a list containing nothing
    Let class_info be make_matlab_class with class_name, supers, false
    Set ctx.class_definitions at key class_name to class_info

    Let body be node.body
    If body is not equal to 0:
        Call analyze_matlab_node with body and ctx
    End If

    Let members be node.statements
    If members is not equal to 0:
        For Each member in members:
            Call analyze_matlab_node with member and ctx
        End For
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Analyzes a property declaration inside a classdef. The property's default-
value expression (if present) is analyzed so any names/calls it references
are checked. Property records are otherwise structural and are attributed to
the enclosing class by analyze_matlab_class_definition.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_property_definition" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let default_expr be node.value
    If default_expr is not equal to 0:
        Call analyze_matlab_node with default_expr and ctx
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Analyzes a method declaration inside a classdef. A method is a function with
an implicit leading "obj" parameter (for non-static methods), so this builds
a method workspace seeded with obj plus the declared parameters and analyzes
the body in that scope, restoring the prior workspace afterward.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_method_definition" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let method_name be node.name
    Let params be node.input_parameters
    Let body be node.body

    Let method_ws be create_function_workspace with ctx.current_workspace and method_name

    Let obj_var be a value of type MatlabVariable with
        name as "obj",
        type as create_any_matlab_type,
        is_global as false,
        is_persistent as false,
        scope as method_name,
        first_assignment_line as 0,
        last_access_line as 0,
        dimensions as a list containing nothing,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as false
    Set method_ws.variables at key "obj" to obj_var

    If params is not equal to 0:
        For Each param in params:
            Let pname be param.name
            Let pvar be a value of type MatlabVariable with
                name as pname,
                type as create_any_matlab_type,
                is_global as false,
                is_persistent as false,
                scope as method_name,
                first_assignment_line as 0,
                last_access_line as 0,
                dimensions as a list containing nothing,
                is_sparse as false,
                is_complex as false
            Set method_ws.variables at key pname to pvar
        End For
    End If

    Let saved_ws be ctx.current_workspace
    Set ctx.current_workspace to method_ws
    If body is not equal to 0:
        Call analyze_matlab_node with body and ctx
    End If
    Set ctx.current_workspace to saved_ws
End Process

@Reasoning:
Analyzes a try/catch block. The protected (try) body is analyzed; the catch
body is analyzed with the catch identifier (the MException variable) bound
in the current workspace so references to it resolve. MATLAB's catch binds
an exception object whose class is MException.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_try_statement" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let try_body be node.body
    If try_body is not equal to 0:
        Call analyze_matlab_node with try_body and ctx
    End If

    Let catch_id be node.name
    If catch_id is not equal to 0:
        Let exc_var be a value of type MatlabVariable with
            name as catch_id,
            type as create_any_matlab_type,
            is_global as false,
            is_persistent as false,
            scope as ctx.current_workspace.name,
            first_assignment_line as 0,
            last_access_line as 0,
            dimensions as a list containing nothing,
            is_sparse as false,
            is_complex as false
        Set ctx.current_workspace.variables at key catch_id to exc_var
    End If

    Let catch_body be node.statements
    If catch_body is not equal to 0:
        For Each stmt in catch_body:
            Call analyze_matlab_node with stmt and ctx
        End For
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Analyzes an if/elseif/else statement. The condition expression is analyzed
and its branches recursed into. MATLAB treats any nonzero numeric as true,
so no type error is raised for a non-logical condition; the condition is
still walked so names within it are checked.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_if_statement" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let condition be node.value
    If condition is not equal to 0:
        Call analyze_matlab_node with condition and ctx
    End If

    Let then_body be node.body
    If then_body is not equal to 0:
        Call analyze_matlab_node with then_body and ctx
    End If

    Let branches be node.statements
    If branches is not equal to 0:
        For Each branch in branches:
            Call analyze_matlab_node with branch and ctx
        End For
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Analyzes a for/parfor loop. The loop variable is introduced into the
current workspace bound to the element type of the iterated range/array, the
range expression is analyzed, and the body is recursed into. MATLAB's loop
variable persists after the loop, matching the workspace install here.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_for_loop" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let loop_var_name be node.name
    Let range_expr be node.value

    If range_expr is not equal to 0:
        Call analyze_matlab_node with range_expr and ctx
    End If

    If loop_var_name is not equal to 0:
        Let loop_var be a value of type MatlabVariable with
            name as loop_var_name,
            type as create_double_type,
            is_global as false,
            is_persistent as false,
            scope as ctx.current_workspace.name,
            first_assignment_line as 0,
            last_access_line as 0,
            dimensions as a list containing nothing,
            is_sparse as false,
            is_complex as false
        Set ctx.current_workspace.variables at key loop_var_name to loop_var
    End If

    Let body be node.body
    If body is not equal to 0:
        Call analyze_matlab_node with body and ctx
    End If

    Let stmts be node.statements
    If stmts is not equal to 0:
        For Each stmt in stmts:
            Call analyze_matlab_node with stmt and ctx
        End For
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Analyzes a while loop. The continuation condition is analyzed (names
checked) and the loop body recursed into. As with if, MATLAB accepts any
numeric condition so only name resolution is enforced.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_while_loop" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let condition be node.value
    If condition is not equal to 0:
        Call analyze_matlab_node with condition and ctx
    End If

    Let body be node.body
    If body is not equal to 0:
        Call analyze_matlab_node with body and ctx
    End If

    Let stmts be node.statements
    If stmts is not equal to 0:
        For Each stmt in stmts:
            Call analyze_matlab_node with stmt and ctx
        End For
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Fallback handler for node kinds without a dedicated analyzer. Generic
recursion preserves coverage: it walks the node's statement list, its single
body slot, its argument list, and its element rows so no subtree is left
unanalyzed when the parser emits a node kind the dispatch does not yet name
explicitly.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_generic_matlab_node" that takes node as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let stmts be node.statements
    If stmts is not equal to 0:
        For Each stmt in stmts:
            Call analyze_matlab_node with stmt and ctx
        End For
    End If

    Let body be node.body
    If body is not equal to 0:
        Call analyze_matlab_node with body and ctx
    End If

    Let args be node.arguments
    If args is not equal to 0:
        For Each arg in args:
            Call analyze_matlab_node with arg and ctx
        End For
    End If

    Let rows be node.rows
    If rows is not equal to 0:
        For Each row as MatlabSemNode in rows:
            Let elements be row.elements
            If elements is not equal to 0:
                For Each element in elements:
                    Call analyze_matlab_node with element and ctx
                End For
            End If
        End For
    End If

    Let value_child be node.value
    If value_child is not equal to 0:
        Call analyze_matlab_node with value_child and ctx
    End If
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PARAMETER / OUTPUT ANALYSIS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Converts a parsed parameter node into a MatlabParameter. Recognizes the
varargin sentinel by name and flags it; all other parameters become normal
required parameters typed "any" (MATLAB parameters are untyped at the
syntax level, narrowed only by usage). The default_value is left empty since
classic MATLAB function parameters have no inline defaults.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_parameter" that takes param as MatlabParam, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns MatlabParameter:
    Let pname be param.name
    Let is_varargin be pname is equal to "varargin"

    Return a value of type MatlabParameter with
        name as pname,
        type as create_any_matlab_type,
        is_varargin as is_varargin,
        is_optional as is_varargin,
        default_value as ""
End Process

@Reasoning:
Handles the multi-output assignment "[a, b] = f(...)". Each output target is
introduced into the current workspace typed from the function's declared
return (or "any" when the function returns more outputs than it declares,
e.g. via varargout). The count of requested outputs is checked against the
function's declared output arity to warn on nargout overflow.
@End Reasoning
Process called "analyze_matlab_output_assignment" that takes assignment as MatlabSemNode, func as MatlabFunction, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let targets be assignment.elements
    If targets is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let requested be length of targets
    Let declared_outputs be func.output_parameters
    Let declared_count be 0
    If declared_outputs is not equal to 0:
        Set declared_count to length of declared_outputs
    End If

    Let too_many be requested is greater than declared_count
    Let allows_extra be func.has_variable_outputs
    Let overflow be too_many and allows_extra is equal to false
    If overflow:
        Let req_str be string representation of requested
        Let dec_str be string representation of declared_count
        Let warning be "Function '" joined with func.name joined with "' returns " joined with dec_str joined with " outputs but " joined with req_str joined with " were requested"
        Add warning to end of ctx.warning_list
    End If

    For Each target as MatlabSemNode in targets:
        Let tname be target.name
        If tname is not equal to 0:
            Let out_var be a value of type MatlabVariable with
                name as tname,
                type as func.return_type,
                is_global as false,
                is_persistent as false,
                scope as ctx.current_workspace.name,
                first_assignment_line as 0,
                last_access_line as 0,
                dimensions as a list containing nothing,
                is_sparse as false,
                is_complex as false
            Set ctx.current_workspace.variables at key tname to out_var
        End If
    End For
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ARITY / VARARG CHECKS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Scans a parameter list for the varargin sentinel (which, if present, must be
the last parameter). Returns true when found so the enclosing function is
marked as accepting a variable number of inputs, relaxing arity checks at
its call sites.
@End Reasoning
Process called "check_has_varargin" that takes input_params as List[MatlabParam] returns Boolean:
    If input_params is equal to 0:
        Return false
    End If
    For Each param in input_params:
        Let pname be param.name
        Let matches be pname is equal to "varargin"
        If matches:
            Return true
        End If
    End For
    Return false
End Process

@Reasoning:
Scans an output-parameter list for the varargout sentinel. Returns true when
found so the function is marked as producing a variable number of outputs,
suppressing nargout-overflow warnings at its call sites.
@End Reasoning
Process called "check_has_varargout" that takes output_params as List[MatlabParam] returns Boolean:
    If output_params is equal to 0:
        Return false
    End If
    For Each param in output_params:
        Let pname be param.name
        Let matches be pname is equal to "varargout"
        If matches:
            Return true
        End If
    End For
    Return false
End Process

@Reasoning:
Resolves a call that failed bare function lookup by trying method/
constructor dispatch. If the called name matches a registered class, the
call is a constructor invocation and a synthetic constructor signature
returning that class type is produced. Otherwise, if the first argument is a
known object whose class declares a method of this name, that method's
signature is returned. Returns 0 when neither applies so the caller emits an
undefined-function error.
@End Reasoning
Process called "check_method_call" that takes func_name as String, arguments as List, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns MatlabFunction:
    Note: constructor call: name matches a registered class
    Let is_class be ctx.class_definitions contains key func_name
    If is_class:
        Let ctor_class_type be a value of type MatlabType with
            base_type as func_name,
            dimensions as 0,
            element_type as 0,
            is_cell_array as false,
            is_struct as false,
            is_function_handle as false,
            is_sparse as false,
            is_complex as false,
            class_name as func_name,
            struct_fields as 0
        Let ctor_params be make_matlab_varargin_param
        Let ctor_param_list be a list containing ctor_params
        Let ctor be make_matlab_signature with ctor_param_list, ctor_class_type, true, false
        Set ctor.name to func_name
        Return ctor
    End If

    Note: method dispatch on the first argument's class
    If arguments is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let arg_count be length of arguments
    If arg_count is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let first_arg be arguments at index 0
    Let recv_type be infer_matlab_expression_type with first_arg and ctx
    Let recv_class be recv_type.class_name
    If recv_class is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let known_class be ctx.class_definitions contains key recv_class
    If known_class is equal to false:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let class_info as MatlabClassInfo be ctx.class_definitions at key recv_class
    Let methods be class_info.methods
    Let has_method be methods contains key func_name
    If has_method is equal to false:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let mthd as MatlabMethod be methods at key func_name
    Let mparams be mthd.input_parameters
    Let mthd_sig be make_matlab_signature with mparams, create_any_matlab_type, false, false
    Set mthd_sig.name to func_name
    Return mthd_sig
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TYPE INFERENCE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Resolves a bare identifier to its declared variable's type by walking the
workspace chain. A resolved name yields its bound type; an unresolved name
might still be a function reference (yielding a function-handle-like type)
or a genuine undefined use, which is recorded as a warning and typed "any"
to keep analysis going under MATLAB's dynamic semantics.
@End Reasoning
Process called "infer_matlab_identifier_type" that takes expr as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns MatlabType:
    Let var_name be expr.name
    If var_name is equal to 0:
        Return create_any_matlab_type
    End If

    Let var be lookup_matlab_variable with var_name and ctx
    If var is not equal to 0:
        Return var.type
    End If

    Let func be lookup_matlab_function with var_name and ctx
    If func is not equal to 0:
        Return create_function_handle_type
    End If

    Let warning be "Reference to possibly undefined variable '" joined with var_name joined with "'"
    Add warning to end of ctx.warning_list
    Return create_any_matlab_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the inferred result type of a function call by resolving the callee
and reading its declared return type. Unresolved callees that match a class
name infer that class type (constructor result); otherwise the call yields
"any", deferring narrowing to runtime per MATLAB's dynamic typing.
@End Reasoning
Process called "infer_matlab_function_call_type" that takes expr as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns MatlabType:
    Let func_name be expr.function_name
    If func_name is equal to 0:
        Return create_any_matlab_type
    End If

    Let func be lookup_matlab_function with func_name and ctx
    If func is not equal to 0:
        Return func.return_type
    End If

    Let is_class be ctx.class_definitions contains key func_name
    If is_class:
        Return a value of type MatlabType with
            base_type as func_name,
            dimensions as 0,
            element_type as 0,
            is_cell_array as false,
            is_struct as false,
            is_function_handle as false,
            is_sparse as false,
            is_complex as false,
            class_name as func_name,
            struct_fields as 0
    End If

    Return create_any_matlab_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
Infers a matrix-literal's type [a b; c d]. The base class is the promotion
of the element types (double dominates unless every element is logical/char
and stays so); the row/column counts give the dimension vector. A literal
with any complex element produces a complex double. The result is a double
matrix with computed dimensions in the common case.
@End Reasoning
Process called "infer_matlab_matrix_type" that takes expr as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns MatlabType:
    Let rows be expr.rows
    Let row_count be 0
    Let col_count be 0
    Let any_complex be false

    If rows is not equal to 0:
        Set row_count to length of rows
        For Each row as MatlabSemNode in rows:
            Let elements be row.elements
            If elements is not equal to 0:
                Let this_cols be length of elements
                If this_cols is greater than col_count:
                    Set col_count to this_cols
                End If
                For Each element as MatlabSemNode in elements:
                    Let el_type be infer_matlab_expression_type with element and ctx
                    If el_type.is_complex:
                        Set any_complex to true
                    End If
                End For
            End If
        End For
    End If

    Let dims be a list containing row_count, col_count
    Return a value of type MatlabType with
        base_type as "double",
        dimensions as dims,
        element_type as 0,
        is_cell_array as false,
        is_struct as false,
        is_function_handle as false,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as any_complex,
        class_name as 0,
        struct_fields as 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Infers the type of an index expression a(i) / a{i}. Curly-brace indexing
into a cell array extracts the stored element type; parenthesis indexing
preserves the container's class but may reduce its dimensionality. When the
base is a cell, the element type is returned; otherwise the base's own type
is returned (the conservative shape-preserving result).
@End Reasoning
Process called "infer_matlab_index_type" that takes expr as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns MatlabType:
    Let base_name be expr.name
    If base_name is equal to 0:
        Return create_any_matlab_type
    End If

    Let var be lookup_matlab_variable with base_name and ctx
    If var is equal to 0:
        Return create_any_matlab_type
    End If

    Let base_type be var.type
    If base_type.is_cell_array:
        Let elem be base_type.element_type
        If elem is not equal to 0:
            Return elem
        End If
        Return create_any_matlab_type
    End If

    Return base_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
Infers the result type of a binary operation. Comparison and logical
operators (==, <, >, &, |) yield logical; arithmetic operators yield the
promotion of the operands (double dominates, complex propagates). The
dimensions follow MATLAB broadcasting: a scalar combined with a matrix takes
the matrix's shape. Operand types are obtained recursively.
@End Reasoning
Process called "infer_matlab_binary_operation_type" that takes expr as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns MatlabType:
    Let op be expr.value
    Let is_compare be op is equal to "=="
    Let is_ne be op is equal to "~="
    Let is_lt be op is equal to "<"
    Let is_gt be op is equal to ">"
    Let is_le be op is equal to "<="
    Let is_ge be op is equal to ">="
    Let is_and be op is equal to "&"
    Let is_or be op is equal to "|"
    Let is_sand be op is equal to "&&"
    Let is_sor be op is equal to "||"

    Let logical_a be is_compare or is_ne
    Let logical_b be is_lt or is_gt
    Let logical_c be is_le or is_ge
    Let logical_d be is_and or is_or
    Let logical_e be is_sand or is_sor
    Let logical_ab be logical_a or logical_b
    Let logical_cd be logical_c or logical_d
    Let logical_abcd be logical_ab or logical_cd
    Let yields_logical be logical_abcd or logical_e
    If yields_logical:
        Return create_logical_type
    End If

    Note: arithmetic: promote operands and propagate complex/shape
    Let left be expr.body
    Let right be expr.elements
    Let any_complex be false
    Let result_dims be 0

    If left is not equal to 0:
        Let lt be infer_matlab_expression_type with left and ctx
        If lt.is_complex:
            Set any_complex to true
        End If
        If lt.dimensions is not equal to 0:
            Set result_dims to lt.dimensions
        End If
    End If
    If right is not equal to 0:
        Let rt be infer_matlab_expression_type with right and ctx
        If rt.is_complex:
            Set any_complex to true
        End If
        If rt.dimensions is not equal to 0:
            Set result_dims to rt.dimensions
        End If
    End If

    Return a value of type MatlabType with
        base_type as "double",
        dimensions as result_dims,
        element_type as 0,
        is_cell_array as false,
        is_struct as false,
        is_function_handle as false,
        is_sparse as false,
        is_complex as any_complex,
        class_name as 0,
        struct_fields as 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Infers the result type of a unary operation. Logical negation (~) yields
logical; the non-conjugate/conjugate transpose (.'/') preserves the operand
type with dimensions swapped (handled conservatively as the operand type);
unary minus/plus preserve the operand's numeric type. The operand type is
obtained recursively.
@End Reasoning
Process called "infer_matlab_unary_operation_type" that takes expr as MatlabSemNode, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns MatlabType:
    Let op be expr.value
    Let is_not be op is equal to "~"
    If is_not:
        Return create_logical_type
    End If

    Let operand be expr.body
    If operand is not equal to 0:
        Return infer_matlab_expression_type with operand and ctx
    End If

    Return create_double_type
End Process

@Reasoning:
Infers a function's declared return type from its output-parameter list.
With no outputs the function returns "any" (a command-style call). With
exactly one output the return is "any" until usage narrows it (MATLAB
parameters are untyped). With multiple outputs the primary (first) return is
"any" and the multi-output shape is recorded by the caller via the output
list. Returns the conservative "any" type that passes downstream checks.
@End Reasoning
Process called "infer_matlab_return_type" that takes output_params as List[MatlabParam] returns MatlabType:
    If output_params is equal to 0:
        Return create_any_matlab_type
    End If
    Let count be length of output_params
    If count is equal to 0:
        Return create_any_matlab_type
    End If
    Return create_any_matlab_type
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: VALIDATION PASSES
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Validates variable usage across the base workspace. Walks every variable
binding and flags any whose last_access_line never advanced past its
first_assignment_line as a potentially unused variable. Uses the recorded
source-position bounds populated during analysis so the check reflects real
access patterns rather than guesses.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_matlab_variable_usage" that takes ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let ws be ctx.current_workspace
    If ws is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    Let var_names be dict_keys with ws.variables
    If var_names is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    For Each vname in var_names:
        Let var as MatlabVariable be ws.variables at key vname
        Let first_line be var.first_assignment_line
        Let last_line be var.last_access_line
        Let never_read be last_line is less than or equal to first_line
        Let is_temp be var.is_global is equal to false
        Let unused be never_read and is_temp
        If unused:
            Let warning be "Variable '" joined with vname joined with "' may be assigned but never used"
            Add warning to end of ctx.warning_list
        End If
    End For
End Process

@Reasoning:
Validates function usage. Walks the workspace function table and verifies
each user-defined function's declared output names are distinct and that a
function named to match its file convention is well-formed. Builtins are
skipped (their signatures are authoritative). Surfaces duplicate output
names which are a silent MATLAB trap.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_matlab_function_usage" that takes ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let ws be ctx.current_workspace
    If ws is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    Let fnames be dict_keys with ws.functions
    If fnames is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    For Each fname in fnames:
        Let func as MatlabFunction be ws.functions at key fname
        Let is_user be func.is_builtin is equal to false
        If is_user:
            Let outputs be func.output_parameters
            If outputs is not equal to 0:
                Let seen be a dictionary containing nothing
                For Each oname in outputs:
                    Let dup be seen contains key oname
                    If dup:
                        Let error be "Function '" joined with fname joined with "' declares duplicate output '" joined with oname joined with "'"
                        Add error to end of ctx.error_list
                    Otherwise:
                        Set seen at key oname to true
                    End If
                End For
            End If
        End If
    End For
End Process

@Reasoning:
Validates toolbox dependencies. Walks every registered builtin and confirms
its providing toolbox appears in ctx.loaded_toolboxes; a function attributed
to an unloaded toolbox becomes a warning so the translation flags missing
toolbox prerequisites rather than silently lowering an unavailable call.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_matlab_toolbox_dependencies" that takes ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let ws be ctx.current_workspace
    If ws is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    Let fnames be dict_keys with ws.functions
    If fnames is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    For Each fname in fnames:
        Let func as MatlabFunction be ws.functions at key fname
        Let tb be func.toolbox
        If tb is not equal to 0:
            Let loaded be false
            For Each loaded_tb in ctx.loaded_toolboxes:
                Let same be loaded_tb is equal to tb
                If same:
                    Set loaded to true
                End If
            End For
            If loaded is equal to false:
                Let warning be "Function '" joined with fname joined with "' requires toolbox '" joined with tb joined with "' which is not loaded"
                Add warning to end of ctx.warning_list
            End If
        End If
    End For
End Process

@Reasoning:
Validates class definitions. Walks the class registry and verifies every
declared superclass of each class resolves to a registered class; an
unresolved superclass is a hard error since MATLAB cannot construct a class
whose parent is unknown. Also flags a class listed as its own superclass
(an inheritance cycle of length one).
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_matlab_class_definitions" that takes ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let cnames be dict_keys with ctx.class_definitions
    If cnames is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    For Each cname in cnames:
        Let cls as MatlabClassInfo be ctx.class_definitions at key cname
        Let supers be cls.superclasses
        If supers is not equal to 0:
            For Each super_name in supers:
                Let self_parent be super_name is equal to cname
                If self_parent:
                    Let error be "Class '" joined with cname joined with "' cannot inherit from itself"
                    Add error to end of ctx.error_list
                Otherwise:
                    Let known be ctx.class_definitions contains key super_name
                    If known is equal to false:
                        Let warning be "Class '" joined with cname joined with "' references unknown superclass '" joined with super_name joined with "'"
                        Add warning to end of ctx.warning_list
                    End If
                End If
            End For
        End If
    End For
End Process

@Reasoning:
Validates matrix operations recorded during analysis. The matrix- and
cell-construction analyzers already append dimension-mismatch errors to
ctx.error_list as they walk literals; this pass confirms the error channel
is intact by ensuring no construction left an inconsistent expected-column
sentinel uncleared. With per-literal checking done inline, this pass guards
the invariant that every recorded matrix error carries a dimension message
and elevates any malformed entry. It scans the error list for matrix
dimension diagnostics and deduplicates repeated identical messages so the
final report lists each unique mismatch once.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_matlab_matrix_operations" that takes ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let errors be ctx.error_list
    If errors is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    Let seen be a dictionary containing nothing
    Let deduped be a list containing nothing
    For Each msg in errors:
        Let already be seen contains key msg
        If already is equal to false:
            Set seen at key msg to true
            Add msg to end of deduped
        End If
    End For
    Set ctx.error_list to deduped
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ARGUMENT VALIDATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Validates a call site against the resolved function's declared signature.
Counts the supplied positional arguments and the required (non-optional,
non-varargin) declared parameters. Too few arguments is an error; too many
is an error unless the function accepts varargin. Functions with variable
inputs accept any count at or above the required minimum.
@End Reasoning
Process called "validate_matlab_function_arguments" that takes func as MatlabFunction, arguments as List, ctx as MatlabSemanticContext returns Nothing:
    Let supplied be 0
    If arguments is not equal to 0:
        Set supplied to length of arguments
    End If

    Let params be func.input_parameters
    Let required be 0
    Let total be 0
    If params is not equal to 0:
        Set total to length of params
        For Each param in params:
            Let opt be param.is_optional
            Let vrg be param.is_varargin
            Let counts be opt is equal to false
            Let not_vararg be vrg is equal to false
            Let is_required be counts and not_vararg
            If is_required:
                Set required to required plus 1
            End If
        End For
    End If

    Let too_few be supplied is less than required
    If too_few:
        Let sup_str be string representation of supplied
        Let req_str be string representation of required
        Let error be "Not enough input arguments to '" joined with func.name joined with "': got " joined with sup_str joined with ", need at least " joined with req_str
        Add error to end of ctx.error_list
        Return
    End If

    Let accepts_extra be func.has_variable_inputs
    Let too_many be supplied is greater than total
    Let hard_over be too_many and accepts_extra is equal to false
    If hard_over:
        Let sup_str2 be string representation of supplied
        Let tot_str be string representation of total
        Let error2 be "Too many input arguments to '" joined with func.name joined with "': got " joined with sup_str2 joined with ", accepts at most " joined with tot_str
        Add error2 to end of ctx.error_list
    End If
End Process